OCI Co. rose to a record in Seoul
trading after announcing a plan to spend 1.8 trillion won ($1.7
billion) on expanding its polysilicon output capacity.   The shares gained 6.0 percent to 549,000 won as of 2:36
p.m. on the  Korea  Exchange, while Koreaâ€™s benchmark Kospi stock
index advanced 2.1 percent.  The money will be used to build a plant in Saemangeum
industrial complex, which can produce 24,000 metric tons a year
of the material used to make solar-panel cells, according to a
regulatory filing from the company.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
